   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GERMANY-U.S.-ASSESS (Berlin) _ On eve of President Clinton's
arrival in Germany, a look at U.S.-German relationship. Germans
feel that when they take a stronger role, as urged by U.S. and
others, they're being slapped down for being too aggressive. By
Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-JUSTICE (Moradabad, India) _ If, as the adage goes,
justice delayed is justice denied, then India's courts can be said
to customarily live in a state of denial. Some 25 million cases are
pending, a breathtaking pileup of the untried accused and
unsatisfied aggrieved. By one expert's calculation, if no new
actions are filed, 324 years would be needed to clear the dockets.
By Barry Bearak.
</P>
