giant leap in understanding the prime scourge of audiences for
opera, theater and concerts _ the crinkling and crackling of candy
wrappers. But their work will be scant help to audiences maddened
by the noise. The scientists demonstrated what plenty of dismayed
concertgoers have already intuited: The noise is inevitable no
matter how the candy is opened. By James Glanz.
