<HEADER>
A1672 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-FASHION-SURVEY0602-CO     06-01 0991
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FASHION-SURVEY0602-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mama mia, you love Sophia!
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Why do readers admire Sophia Loren's style?
If you have to ask, you'll never know.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why? Are you kidding?'' says Ann Fintz of West Palm Beach.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't ask why! It's just there!'' says Suzanne Cohen of West
Palm Beach.
</P>
<P>
   In our recent fashion survey of readers, the luscious Loren, who
turns 66 this September, topped the favorite celebrity style
category.
</P>
<P>
   Readers gaze admiringly at a constellation of stars, ranging
from Gardens mall spokesmodel Lauren Hutton (``classic, simple and
unassuming'') to rapper Mary J. Blige (``dresses really nice with
the classy clothes'').
</P>
<P>
   From Secretary of State Madeleine Albright (``neat, tailored,
not dowdy'') to singing talk show host Marie Osmond (``her dress at
the Miss America pageant was to die for!'').
</P>
<P>
   From perky actress Meg Ryan (``simple . . . but with a slight
sexiness'') to Senate candidate Hillary Rodham Clinton (``great
suits'').
</P>
<P>
   Other multiple mentions: Dina Merrill, Ann Currie, Julia
Roberts, Gwyneth Paltrow and Hollywood youngsters Jennifer Love
Hewitt, Keri Russell, Sarah Michelle Gellar and Reese Witherspoon.
</P>
<P>
   We asked celebrity stylist Phillip Bloch, whose clients include
Salma Hayek, Cindy Crawford, Jim Carrey and Jenna Elfman, to
deconstruct what the top vote-getters do and the way that they do
it.
</P>
<P>
   SOPHIA LOREN
</P>
<P>
   WHAT READERS SAY:
</P>
<P>
   ``Dresses in good taste,'' says Sandra Lucca.
</P>
<P>
   ``She looks so mature and calm,'' says Angela Ward. ``She's such
a beautiful person.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Smart and sexy,'' says Connie Valente of Wellington.
</P>
<P>
   ``Her clothing looks sharp but comfortable,'' says Marla
Massman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I love the classy but sexy hourglass look,'' says Andrea
Parvin. ``She's always perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   What the stylist says:
</P>
<P>
   ``She's just incredibly chic. She still works her best assets,
and yet she's not vulgar about it.
</P>
<P>
   ``She wears the right shapes for herself. She doesn't try to
dress too young, too old or too loud. She's very tasteful.''
</P>
<P>
   What we can learn from Sophia:
</P>
<P>
   Dress your age.
</P>
<P>
   ``She definitely looks sexy, with her large breasts and curvy
figure,'' Bloch says. ``She accentuates that _ not like a woman of
20 would but like a woman her age would.''
</P>
<P>
   CHER
</P>
<P>
   WHAT READERS SAY:
</P>
<P>
   ``She always looks so special and sexy,'' says Terry Kline.
</P>
<P>
   ``She so doesn't care what people think,'' says Diana Goodwill
Brovero.
</P>
<P>
   ``She is lucky enough to be able to wear those outrageous
outfits,'' says Suzi Lavati.
</P>
<P>
   What the stylist says:
</P>
<P>
   ``Good lord! She travels to the beat of her own drummer, and I
think that's what people admire about her. She does what she wants
when she wants.
</P>
<P>
   ``She just is what she is. . . . Cher will show every part of
her body, and we love that about her.''
</P>
<P>
   What we can learn from Cher:
</P>
<P>
   Be yourself and have the courage of your convictions.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's not afraid, and that's what people like,'' Bloch says.
``She has the charisma to pull that off.''
</P>
<P>
   BARBRA STREISAND
</P>
<P>
   WHAT READERS SAY:
</P>
<P>
   ``Elegant,'' says Barbara Weisser, ``especially in casual
clothes.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Tailored look,'' says Irene Wainick.
</P>
<P>
   ``She always looks elegant and sleek,'' says Ellin Berger.
</P>
<P>
   What the stylist says:
</P>
<P>
   ``She goes for casual chic,'' Bloch says. ``She's casual enough.
She's not over the top.''
</P>
<P>
   Furthermore, ``Barbra is very convinced about what she feels is
right about her, and so she really works those points.''
</P>
<P>
   According to Bloch, Barbra likes her legs, shoulders and neck,
but prefers to camouflage her waist.
</P>
<P>
   What we can learn from Barbra:
</P>
<P>
   Know what works for you.
</P>
<P>
   Barbra isn't very adventurous with color, cleaving to the
cleanness of black, white or gray.
</P>
<P>
   (The right connections help: One of Barbra's best pals is
designer Donna Karan. ``She's got a good friend in the business,''
Bloch says.)
</P>
<P>
   HALLE BERRY
</P>
<P>
   WHAT READERS SAY:
</P>
<P>
   ``She is always sophisticated and sexy-looking, whether in jeans
or a gown,'' says Kimberly Frantantoni.
</P>
<P>
   ``Always dressed to the nines,'' says Marcia Billhartz.
</P>
<P>
   ``Casual, yet stylish and fashionable,'' says Arma Velasquez.
</P>
<P>
   What the stylist says:
</P>
<P>
   ``She's my client _ I dress her all the time. She can look
beautiful in anything. . . . She can go from Doris Day to Natalie
Wood to Brigitte Bardot. She covers all the bases.''
</P>
<P>
   Berry looks luminous in a range of colors, and also looks as
comfortable in a dressy Valentino as in avant-garde Comme des
Garcons.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's well-rounded, which is why I think she appeals to
people.''
</P>
<P>
   What we can learn from Halle:
</P>
<P>
   Celebrate what you've got, but don't flaunt it.
</P>
<P>
   Berry has a feminine, curvy body, ``but you don't think of her
as a sex symbol,'' Bloch says. Because she's not pigeonholed as a
sex goddess, her style can run the gamut.
</P>
<P>
   GRACE KELLY AND AUDREY HEPBURN
</P>
<P>
   WHAT READERS SAY:
</P>
<P>
   About Audrey _ ``I like simplicity, not frills,'' says Mindy
Presler of Hobe Sound.
</P>
<P>
   ``Total elegance,'' says Jane Muller of Lake Park.
</P>
<P>
   ``Beauty, harmony, simplicity incarnate,'' says Enid Sefcovic of
Lake Worth.
</P>
<P>
   About Grace _ ``Refined and dignified,'' says a Delray Beach
reader.
</P>
<P>
   ``She wore simple, elegant, graceful clothes that said, `I'm
Grace Kelly _ STAR!','' says Suzanne Seely of Jupiter.
</P>
<P>
   What the stylist says:
</P>
<P>
   Simple, classic and timeless. ``The gowns that Grace Kelly wore
are like the one Hilary Swank wore to the Oscars. . . The shift
dresses that Audrey Hepburn made famous are still good now. You can
wear them to the office, you can wear them to breakfast at
Tiffany's.''
</P>
<P>
   What we can learn from Grace and Audrey:
</P>
<P>
   Study up and major in the classics.
</P>
<P>
   Bloch says, ``I personally use them as style guides for my girls
many times.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
