<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES FOUR COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   TWO DECADES OF CNN: It has been two decades since Ted Turner
launched his news operation in the basement of a converted Atlanta
country club. The 20-year period has been marked by highs such as
the Persian Gulf War's ``Boys of Baghdad,'' worldwide growth into
212 countries and expansion on the Internet. Yet today, a struggle
with ratings, unrest over a major merger and an uncertain online
future challenge the 24-hour news network. (Includes a 6-column
photo of the lobby of the CNN Center, a 2-column photo of
journalists working in the newsroom, a 1-column photo of employees
working at CNN Interactive and an 18-pica photo of CNN chairman Tom
Johnson.)
</P>
</TEXT>
