York Times News Service. Stories are for release Friday, June 2,
2000, unless otherwise embargoed.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   CNN-PARTY _ ATLANTA _ Coverage of CNN's 20th anniversary
celebration at Philips Arena, an invitation-only party for about
15,000. In the audience will be lots of old CNN hands, advertisers
and cable operators who supported the network in its early years
when it was struggling, and big names from Queen Noor of Jordan to
former President Jimmy Carter. Diana Ross will be the entertainer
for the event. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   FREEDOM-TRAIL _ BOSTON _ We walk the 2 1/2-mile Freedom Trail,
which links more than 20 18th century sites associated with the
American revolution. Our guide is a re-enactor portraying James
Otis, the main who said ``Taxation ... is tyranny.'' (Thrasher,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 4.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   HISTORIC-SITES _ PLYMOUTH, Mass. _ We spend a day amid the
historic sites in the town where the Pilgrims landed in 1620. We
visit Plymouth Plantation, the Mayflower II and, of course, The
Rock. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 4.
</P>
<P>
   BOSTON-FAMILY _ Six great things to do in Boston, including the
Duck Tour, New England Aquarium, whale-watching, etc. This will
also contain IF YOU GO information. Thrasher. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 4.
</P>
<P>
   FREEDOM-FESTIVAL _ Details programming being offered as a part
of celebration of the 225th anniversary of the beginning of the
American Revolution. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 4.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-FESTIVALS _ Southern happenings. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY _ ROBBINSVILLE, N.C. _ A rustic lodge in western North
Carolina is still offering couples a place to unwind almost 60
years after it opened as a mountain vacation spot. Its new owners
have added a twist by marketing to stressed-out suburbanites. Since
Robert and Karen Rankin bought the Snowbird Mountain Lodge four
years ago, they've refined its rustic side and added creature
comforts without too many frills. The Rankins think the surrounding
100 acres of the Nantahala National Forest and Snowbird Mountains
should be entertainment enough for guests. (McQueen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet Travel page for the current week.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL 0530 -- Nowadays, just about any working stiff can
go on a cruise, especially if you don't mind an inside cabin. You
can take a four-night cruise to the Caribbean that includes dining
and dancing for under $500. And, of course, if you have money and
time to spare, you can book a round-the-world, 105-day cruise on
the Queen Elizabeth 2 for just $30,000. Here are some great cruises
for different budgets (Blackerby, Palm Beach Post) Art includes a
3-column color photo of the atrium of a Disney cruise ship, a
2-column color photo of the Queen Elizabeth 2, a 2-column color
photo of a cruise ship in port in Venice, a 2-column color photo of
a dancer on a Carnival cruise ship and a 2-column color photo of
the expensive cruise ship Seaborn Pride.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: WEB SITES BOX: a box of additional travel Web sites for
young travelers. (Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
