lot of speculation about what the president will do when he leaves
office next January as one of the youngest former chief executives
in U.S. history. Former Sen. Dale Bumpers, D-Ark., a longtime
acquaintance of Clinton and one of his chief defenders during the
impeachment trial, thinks he might run for the Senate from
Arkansas. By AUSTIN ZALKIN. (Story will also be filed in the ``p''
category.)
