<P>
   ELIAN RULING
</P>
<P>
   ELIAN-RULING _ ATLANTA _ A federal appeals court sided with
Elian Gonzalez's father today in the 6-month-old international
custody battle, ruling that immigration officials were entitled to
deny an asylum hearing for the Cuban boy. Under the ruling, Elian
must remain in the United States for 14 days to give his Miami
relatives a chance to appeal. (Cook, Atlanta
JNournal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ELIAN _ MIAMI _ Reaction of the Cuban community in Miami to the
appeals court ruling on Elian in Atlanta. (Palm Beach Post). WITH
PHOTO.
</P>
