<P>
   BLACKBEARD _ BEAUFORT, N.C. _ Timbers from the wreck believed to
be Blackbeard's flagship waited 282 years until archaeologists
lifted them to the surface Wednesday. Through 20 feet of
bottle-green water, divers raised four deteriorated wood planks
from the port side of the shipwreck to waiting research vessels.
These pieces of wood may resolve critical mysteries surrounding
Blackbeard's pirate career, including the origin of his ship, the
Queen Anne's Revenge. (Royster, Greenville Daily News). 20. WITH
PHOTOS.
