   &UR; FINANCIAL &LR;  (``f'' code)
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-AIRLINES (Calgary, Alberta) _ After Air Canada's
acquisition of Canadian Airlines this spring, Canadians are waking
up to an airline market more reliant on a single carrier than any
other major Western nation. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-SALES (Detroit) _ Automakers report sales in May, which are
expected to show a decline for the first time since August 1998. By
Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   TV-SURVIVORS (Undated) _ Setting up what could be a battle royal
in the normally sedate summer television season, ``Survivors,''
CBS's much-hyped reality show about people ``stranded'' on a
deserted island, scores a triumph in the ratings Wednesday night,
getting about 15 million viewers and nearly beating
``Millionaire,'' which ABC used to try to squash the debut. The
``Survivors'' success could lead to a spate of new deals for these
kind of shows. One good sign for the show: More people tuned in as
the show went on. By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   NORRIS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The weekly column. By Floyd Norris.
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-PENSIONS (Sao Paulo) _ In a political race that was major
news in Brazil but little noticed abroad, a radical-left coalition
has won two seats on the board of the nation's largest and most
influential pension fund. The change could have a major impact on
the priorities of the 62 major Brazilian companies in which the
fund has a significant stake. By Jennifer L. Rich.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-INSURANCE (Tokyo) _ Prudential Insurance Co. of America is
poised to take a 20 percent stake in the Kyoei Life Insurance Co.,
one of Japan's many faltering life insurers, for about $277
million. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
