<HEADLINE>
OUT ON THE TOWN
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER AND REED JOHNSON 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Don't be surprised if you see something weird in the list of
local venues. Like many other arenas throughout the country, the
former Irvine Meadows Amphitheatre has changed its name _ and gone
blatantly corporate.
</P>
<P>
   The outdoor venue in Laguna Hills is now called the Verizon
Wireless Amphitheatre, the results of a recent merger of three cell
phone companies. But don't worry; it's still the same joint.
</P>
<P>
   Here is a list of forthcoming pop, jazz, classical, theater,
dance and art events.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets for many of these are available through Ticketmaster
locations, which you'll find at all Wherehouse, Tower, Ritmo Latino
and Robinsons-May outlets, unless otherwise stated. To charge by
phone, call (213) 480-3232 or (714) 740-2000.
</P>
<P>
   POP/ROCK/COUNTRY
</P>
<P>
   --Tonight: Matchbox Twenty, Wilshire-Ebell Theatre; Gene,
Troubadour; Jon Brion, Largo.
</P>
<P>
   --Saturday: Apples in Stereo, Troubadour; Chi-Lites, Dramatics,
Harold Melvin's Bluenotes, ``'70s Soul Jam,'' Greek.
</P>
<P>
   --Sunday: Lucy Pearl, House of Blues.
</P>
<P>
   --Monday: Cowboy Junkies, House of Blues.
</P>
<P>
   --Tuesday: Nine Inch Nails, Pond.
</P>
<P>
   --Tuesday-Wednesday: Sleater-Kinney, El Rey; Vic Chesnutt,
Kristen Hersh, the Mint.
</P>
<P>
   --Wednesday: Lou Reed, Universal; Groove Armada, Mayan Theatre;
Average White Band, House of Blues.
</P>
<P>
   --Wednesday-Thursday: Elliott Smith, Palace; Luna, Knitting
Factory.
</P>
<P>
   --Thursday: Primal Scream, House of Blues; Richard Buckner,
Spaceland; Robert Earl Keen, Roxy.
</P>
<P>
   --Thursday-June 9: Modest Mouse, El Rey.
</P>
<P>
   --June 9: 'N Sync, Rose Bowl; Primal Scream, Vynyl; Dropkick
Murphys, Bouncing Souls, Dwarves, ``Punk-O-Rama,'' Palace.
</P>
<P>
   --June 10: Jayhawks, Arcadia; Mission UK, Key Club.
</P>
<P>
   --June 10-11: Mary J. Blige, Universal.
</P>
<P>
   --June 11-12: Magnetic Fields, Knitting Factory.
</P>
<P>
   --June 12: Jayhawks, Troubadour.
</P>
<P>
   --June 13: Emmylou Harris, House of Blues; Juliana Hatfield,
Troubadour.
</P>
<P>
   --June 13-14: Steely Dan, Universal.
</P>
<P>
   --June 14: Todd Rundgren, House of Blues; Remy Zero, Key Club;
Stone Temple Pilots, Santa Barbara Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   --June 15: Flock of Seagulls, 14 Below.
</P>
<P>
   --June 15-16: Violent Femmes, Knitting Factory.
</P>
<P>
   --June 16: Pink Martini, El Rey; Eek-A-Mouse, Roxy; Steely Dan,
Verizon.
</P>
<P>
   --June 16, 18: Dr. Dre, Snoop Dogg, Eminem, Ice Cube, Warren G.,
``Up in Smoke Tour,'' Pond.
</P>
<P>
   --June 17, 19: Dixie Chicks, Patty Griffin, Pond.
</P>
<P>
   --June 17: Creed, Cypress Hill, Eminem, Korn, Limp Bizkit, Moby,
``KROQ Weenie Roast 2000,'' Edison Field, Anaheim; Stan Ridgway,
Roxy; War, House of Blues.
</P>
<P>
   --June 19-20: Marc Anthony, Greek.
</P>
<P>
   --June 20: Robyn Hitchcock, Grant Lee Phillips, Troubadour.
