<HEADLINE>
`MY LITTLE MARGIE' ACTRESS STILL ON THE SCENE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Whatever happened to the actress Gale Storm, who used
to be on the TV series ``Oh! Susanna?''
</P>
<P>
   _ C.B., Fort Worth, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Storm, 78, has made several public appearances recently
at film festivals and other fan events. Earlier this month, she
performed stage productions of ``My Little Margie'' and ``The
Bickersons'' at a radio convention in Brockton, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A native of Bloomington, Texas, the actress and singer was
signed to a movie contract in 1940 after winning a national talent
contest. She married another winner, actor Lee Bonnell.
</P>
<P>
   Storm has appeared in more than 30 films, including ``It
Happened on Fifth Avenue'' and ``G.I. Honeymoon,'' and had the
title role in the '50s TV series ``Oh! Susanna'' and ``My Little
Margie.''
</P>
<P>
   Write to Storm in care of her fan club, the Gale Storm
Appreciation Society, at Box 212, Coalton, OH 45621-0212. The club
has a Web site at sites.netscape.net/galestormsociety.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ The Sears catalog used to offer white carpenter's bib
overalls. Where can I get them today?
</P>
<P>
   _ S.J., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Workingman's Emporium, a clothing retailer in San Jose,
Calif., sells Carhartt painter and drill carpenter overalls.
</P>
<P>
   The overalls are available in an off-white color called
``painter's drill.'' Painter overalls sell for $32.99 and carpenter
overalls sell for $49.99.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call (877) 287-3942 or visit the Web site
www.workingmans.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ How is the actor William McNamara related to Ricky
Nelson?
</P>
<P>
   _ S.P., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ They aren't related, but McNamara hears about their
resemblance often. The sons of Ricky Nelson have approached
McNamara about playing their father in an upcoming movie, McNamara
told TV-Now.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a movie he did with John Wayne, `Rio Bravo,' and there
are some shots in there that I look at, and it's scary,'' McNamara
said. ``He looks like me.''
</P>
<P>
   McNamara, 35, is appearing in the sitcom ``Beggars &AMP; Choosers''
on Showtime. He was also in the films ``Stag,'' ``Surviving the
Game'' and ``Texasville.''
</P>
<P>
   Write to him in care of International Creative Management, 8942
Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90211.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
