<P>
   ELIAN-ASYLUM (Undated) _ The U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in
Atlanta rules that the Immigration and Naturalization Service was
within its rights when it denied an asylum hearing to Elian
Gonzalez. The court say that the father's right to decide is
paramount and that the 6-year-old is too young to make such a
decision himself. By KIM COBB.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-DNA (Austin, Texas) _ We look at how many other death-row
inmates in Texas might seek the same consideration that Gov. George
W. Bush is giving a convicted rapist-murderer, who is asking that
his execution be delayed while he continues to appeal his sentence.
By JOHN GONZALEZ.
