 PERSONALS: That's the Spirit  
 (Eds: Repeating for all needing. This story also moved in the 
 ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Organizers of the Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras 2000 Festival in
England have received an official response from  &UR; Queen Elizabeth &LR; ,
in answer to their plea for a message of support:
</P>
<P>
   ``It is very much hoped that the celebrations ... will be
enjoyable,'' wrote the queen's chief correspondence officer,
 &UR; Deborah Bean &LR; . Organizer  &UR; Peter Tatchell  &LR; called this ``a pleasant
departure from the rather stuffy stance that the Palace has taken
in the past,'' said the Telegraph.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &QL;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ The new Veterans.com site, launched on Memorial Day, includes
a veterans locator database that permits veterans to find long-last
comrades who have registered with the site.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; SEAN YOUNG PLANNING EXCITING COMEBACK &QL;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Temperamental actress  &UR; Sean Young &LR; , who hasn't been seen on the
big screen in a while, showed up at the Cannes Film Festival and
said she has signed a three-movie deal with  &UR; Menahem Golan &LR; , the
man who made  &UR; Pia Zadora &LR;  _ his wife at the time _ a household
word.
</P>
<P>
   She also told Channel One, the British station, that she has
signed a deal with  &UR; Roger Corman  &LR; to direct, including the
possibility of making a movie from a screenplay written by her
plumber. It's ``all about a man who gets cryogenically frozen, and
you see his spirit leave his body and enter a baby boy. Years
later, the frozen man is brought back to life but starts getting
ill because he has no spirit. It's about whether we are just a body
or whether life is about having a soul. I do aura readings! You
take a picture, and I can read the contours.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &QL;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Mr. Peres' mandate seems clear: Infuse Details (magazine) &LR; 
 &UR; with class and decorum and a post-straight, even Eurochic, &LR; 
 &UR; element. An anti-Maxim. But not gay.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ You go, boy. From a New York Observer story about  &UR; Daniel &LR; 
 &UR; Peres &LR; , newly appointed editor of Details magazine.
</P>
