<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBO-BRAVES-YANKEES _ ATLANTA _ Perhaps it's no secret why the
Braves and Yankees have been the class of baseball during the
1990s. In fact, they are mirror images . . . from the eccentric
owners who, for some reason or another, have stepped into the
shadows . . . from two managers, who seem to handle their players
the same way . . . from the players (Rocker aside) who are class
acts in baseball and bring a great deal of professionalism to the
game on and off the field . . . to the farm-system philosophy.
(Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BIGRED-MACHINE _ CINCINNATI _ Immediately after the 1976
Cincinnati Reds, a.k.a., The Big Red Machine, completed a four-game
sweep of the New York Yankees, club president/general manager Bob
Howsam, the construction engineer of The BRM, accepted the trophy
and uttered some prophetic words. The Big Red Machine celebrates
its 25-year anniversary Saturday night. (Dayton Daily News). 22.
</P>
