   SPIES (Washington) _ What the government is doing to counter
spying.
</P>
<P>
   EDUC-SURVEY (Washington) _ An annual survey of American
education released Thursday by the federal government portrays a
nation newly committed to learning at all levels, with more
toddlers in preschool, more high school students going directly to
college, and more adult learners returning to school. The report,
the most comprehensive statistical survey of the nation's schools,
says that students are taking more demanding courses and achieving
at their highest level in mathematics and science since a federal
commission declared a national emergency in education in 1983. By
Kate Zernike.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   SECRET-SERVICE-SUIT (Washington) _ Lawyers for black secret
service agents asked a federal judge Thursday to order a stop to
what they said is retaliation against some agents who are
plaintiffs in a lawsuit accusing the service of racial
discrimination in promotions to the agency's senior ranks. By David
Johnston.
</P>
