But the Supreme Court this week let stand an Oregon law that gives
adults adopted as children the right to see their original birth
certificates, whether their birth parents agree or not. This is
unfair to mothers who gave up their unwanted babies counting on
having their privacy protected. The fear of being confronted later
by an abandoned child may discourage adoptions. By MARIANNE MEANS.
