secret: the crash of 1998, the great financial meltdown that wiped
out Russia's middle class and turned the Kremlin into a global
deadbeat, is over. The Kremlin casts it as real, if still shaky,
and its numbers look promising. By Michael Wines. (Scheduled to
move by 8 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) 2,300 words.
