<HEADLINE>
BILL TO RESTRICT WOMEN AT WESTERN WALL IS BACKED 
</HEADLINE>
 LEAD-WRITETHROUGH-BOS  
 (Eds: Clarifies headline)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ALIZA MARCUS  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ In a move that shows the strains between religious
and secular Jews in Israel, ultra-Orthodox parliamentarians have
won initial support for a bill setting a seven-year jail term for
women who wear prayer shawls and read from Torah scrolls at the
