<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRUMP-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Trump makes estate Mortgage-Lago
</P>
<P>
   By Linda Rawls
</P>
<P>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Donald Trump has mortgaged Mar-a-Lago for
nearly $25 million, Palm Beach County property records show.
</P>
<P>
   Trump took out two loans on the 118-room estate on April 26 _
one for $19,883,870 and one for $5 million _ with Union Labor Life
Insurance Co. of Washington. The loans are payable over 10 years,
Trump said.
</P>
<P>
   Mar-a-Lago has an assessed value of $22.2 million, property
records show. Trump paid $10 million for the former Marjorie
Merriweather Post estate and its furnishings in 1995, and another
$2 million for a beach parcel. Union Labor handled Mar-a-Lago's
original $10 million mortgage in 1995, company Vice President
Herbert Kolben said. He declined to discuss terms of the new loans.
</P>
<P>
   Trump almost had the original mortgage paid off. Before these
new loans, his mortgage was down to $116,130, said Joy Hearn, Palm
Beach County's senior property appraiser. Mortgage records show he
can borrow up to $50 million on the 17-acre property, now a private
club, in the next 20 years.
</P>
<P>
   Newspaper and magazine reports have said Trump needed the money
to help pay a $26 million debt to the financially strapped Trump
Hotels &AMP; Resorts, the casino company he took public to help him pay
off creditors. He borrowed that $26 million to pay a personal loan
to Donaldson Lufkin and Jenrette, the New York investment bank, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
   Trump on Thursday denied he took additional Mar-a-Lago financing
to pay his casino loan, which was due May 15. He said he paid that
off a week early.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mar-a-Lago has always been mortgaged,'' Trump said. ``I've
always had financing in varying amounts, from $25 million to
nothing. ... It's good for tax purposes.''
</P>
<P>
   He said the Mar-a-Lago loans don't mean he's in financial
trouble.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the best year I've ever had in business,'' he said.
``Manhattan real estate has gone up even more than Florida has.''
</P>
<P>
   lindarawls(at)pbpost.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
