NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, JUNE 2
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOREA-MASSACRE-DAILY-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 30,
about Edward Daily, who claimed to have participated in a massacre
of Korean civilians at No Gun Ri in 1950, referred incompletely to
the news organizations that first raised questions about his
account and war record. Those organizations, cited in four earlier
articles in The Times, were the Web site Stripes.com and U.S. News
&AMP; World Report.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-SYRIA-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 31,
about a United Nations envoy's statement that Syria is ready to
accept Israel's retreat from Lebanon as a complete withdrawal
misstated the timing of Security Council Resolution 425, calling
for Israel's withdrawal from Lebanon. It was adopted in 1978, after
Israeli occupied part of southern Lebanon, not in 1982, after
Israel's full-scale invasion of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-GIFFORD-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 24)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Don Gifford, sent by the New York Times News
Service on Wednesday, May 24, listed survivors incompletely. They
also include two stepdaughters _ Holly McLennan Ketron of
Princeton, N.J., and Angelica Syp of Burlington, Vt. _ and four
stepgrandchildren.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-WEATHER-ONLINE-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 31,
about online weather data misstated the Web addresses of two
sites.They are www.aws.com and www.weatherbug.com.
</P>
