<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 23:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2519 &Cx1f; kan-z
r v BC-BC-KAN-BUDGET-KAN &LR;      06-01 0270
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BC-KAN-BUDGET-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for use Friday, June 2.
</P>
<P>
   BRIDG-LINK (Kansas City) _ A bridge too far? Not for Margie
Burton. Who would have thought a 130-pound woman could move four
10-ton bridges 110 miles to the John Redmond Reservoir in Kansas,
opening up thousands of acres to hikers, bikers and horse riders.
The bridges of Coffey County are coming from Clay County, a
donation of Argosy Casino, but the real story is about the power of
one. By Lee Hill Kavanaugh. (Will move in the ``a'' national news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   ROAD-FOREST (Rolla, Mo.) _ A road building ban proposed by
President Clinton for federal forests is gaining attention in
Missouri because of concerns about the Mark Twain National Forest.
By Bill Graham. (Will move in the ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
